    • Method Detail

      • getOwner

        public AbstractContainer getOwner()
        Description copied from class: Element
        Each element can be owned by some other element. When an owner is deleted, it deletes all objects owned by it. A box's owner is a container (or one of its derived classes — another box or diagram), a line is owned by a container. A label is owned by a box, a line, a label or a container. Container's owner is a container. A diagram is not owned by any other element.
        Overrides:
        getOwner in class Element
        Returns:
        the owner of this object, or possibly null, if this element is a diagram.

      • createInsideLabel

        public InsideLabel createInsideLabel(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D.Double rectangle,
                                     LayoutConstraints.ConstraintType constraintType,
                                     double spacing,
                                     java.lang.Integer row,
                                     java.lang.Integer column)
        Description copied from class: AbstractContainer
        Creates a new inside label as a child of this container. The minimum size of the new label is the size of the given rectangle. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.
        Overrides:
        createInsideLabel in class AbstractContainer
        Parameters:
        rectangle - the position of the new label
        constraintType - the type of the layout constraints for the new label
        spacing - the spacing value for the new label
        row - the row of the new label in this container's grid
        column - the column of the new label in this container's grid
        Returns:
        the new inside label object.

      • move

        public void move(java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double newCenter,
                 AbstractContainer newOwner,
                 java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double growPoint,
                 java.lang.Integer row,
                 java.lang.Integer column)
        Moves the label, taking it from its current position and placing it at the given position, along with its children. The actual size may differ due to children. The new owner of the label will be stretched to accommodate the label at its desired new position. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.
        Parameters:
        newCenter - the new desired center of the label
        newOwner - the new owner of the label
        growPoint - the exact point at which to insert the label, it will then be grow from that point to its desired position as per resize(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D.Double)
        row - the row of the label in new owner's grid
        column - the column of the label in new owner's grid

      • resize

        public void resize(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D.Double rectangle)
        Resizes the label, moving it from its current position to the given rectangle, pushing aside other elements as needed. Changes the minimum size of the label to the given size. The actual size may differ due to children. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.
        Parameters:
        rectangle - the new position of the label to resize it to
